[EXPLOSION]

00:17.024 --> 00:21.020
THUS THE POWERPUFF GIRLS
WERE BORN!

00:21.022 --> 00:23.004
USING THEIR ULTRA-SUPERPOWERS,

00:23.006 --> 00:27.005
BLOSSOM, BUBBLES, AND BUTTERCUP
HAVE DEDICATED THEIR LIVES

00:27.007 --> 00:32.021
TO FIGHTING CRIME
AND THE FORCES OF EVIL!

00:58.029 --> 01:04.009
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
TURNER ENTERTAINMENT GROUP
AND U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION

01:17.014 --> 01:21.020
Narrator:
THE CITY OF TOWNSVILLE,

01:24.028 --> 01:26.028
MOM'S HOT APPLE PIE...

01:27.000 --> 01:28.008
HI, BILLY!

01:28.010 --> 01:29.011
HI, MRS. O'HARA.

01:29.013 --> 01:32.016
WHITE PICKET FENCES...

01:32.018 --> 01:33.027
WOW!

01:33.029 --> 01:36.007
AND BASEBALL.

01:38.002 --> 01:42.024
OH, YES, TYPICALLY AMERICAN
IN EVERY WAY.

01:42.026 --> 01:45.005
[ALARM RINGING]

01:45.007 --> 01:46.014
Criminal:
HA HA HA!

01:46.016 --> 01:49.008
THANKS FOR THE LOOT,
SUCKERS.

01:52.021 --> 01:53.027
[LAUGHING]

01:53.029 --> 01:55.003
Narrator:
ONLY ONE THING

01:55.005 --> 01:58.020
SETS TOWNSVILLE APART
FROM THE REST OF AMERICA.

01:58.022 --> 02:01.020
OR SHOULD I SAY 3 THINGS?

02:01.022 --> 02:04.011
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS!

02:06.016 --> 02:08.016
OH, NO!
YOU GUYS GO LEFT.

02:08.018 --> 02:10.023
I'LL TAKE RIGHT.

02:13.001 --> 02:15.018
[GRUNTING]

02:18.004 --> 02:20.018
QUICK,
FASTBALL SPECIAL.

02:30.021 --> 02:34.003
THAT'S RIGHT.
KEEP IT MOVING.

02:36.018 --> 02:39.009
JEEZ LOUISE,
POWERPUFF GIRLS,

02:39.011 --> 02:40.009
YOU DONE IT AGAIN!

02:40.011 --> 02:43.001
Narrator:
YES, THE POWERPUFF GIRLS.

02:43.003 --> 02:45.007
AND IT IS THIS
EXTRAORDINARY FACT

02:45.009 --> 02:46.013
THAT HAS CAUGHT THE EYE

02:46.015 --> 02:49.008
OF NONE OTHER
THAN BERNIE BERNSTEIN,

02:49.010 --> 02:54.015
BIG-TIME HOLLYWOOD DIRECTOR,
PRODUCER, AGENT.

02:56.011 --> 02:57.015
[DIALING PHONE]

02:57.017 --> 02:59.022
DONNIE, SET UP A LUNCH
WITH THE POWERPUFF GIRLS--

02:59.024 --> 03:01.021
SOMETHING QUAINT
AND EXPENSIVE.

03:01.023 --> 03:04.000
YES, SIR.
YOU GOT IT, SIR.

03:10.015 --> 03:13.017
Narrator:
LOOKS LIKE MR. BERNSTEIN'S
GOT SOMETHING BIG PLANNED

03:13.019 --> 03:16.009
FOR OUR 3 LITTLE
SUPERHEROES.

03:16.011 --> 03:18.005
Blossom:
WELL, WHO IS HE?

03:18.007 --> 03:19.006
Professor:
I DON'T KNOW.

03:19.008 --> 03:22.002
HE SAID HIS NAME IS
BERNIE BERNSTEIN.

03:22.004 --> 03:23.007
AND WHAT DID HE SAY?

03:23.009 --> 03:24.002
WELL, NOT MUCH.

03:24.004 --> 03:25.008
HE SAID HE'S
FROM HOLLYWOOD

03:25.010 --> 03:27.007
AND THAT HE'S
REAL EXCITED TO
MEET YOU GUYS.

03:27.009 --> 03:28.011
NOW, DON'T WORRY,
GIRLS.

03:28.013 --> 03:31.001
I'M HERE TO
LOOK OUT FOR YOU.

03:33.021 --> 03:35.005
AH, PROFESSOR UTONIUM!

03:35.007 --> 03:38.003
YOU'RE EXPECTED.
RIGHT THIS WAY.

03:40.008 --> 03:41.010
OVER HERE!

03:41.012 --> 03:42.023
OVER HERE!

03:42.025 --> 03:44.015
SIT, SIT!

03:48.006 --> 03:50.008
EAT, EAT!
IT'S GOOD!

03:50.010 --> 03:52.006
WAITER, WAITER!

03:52.008 --> 03:53.008
MORE FOOD!

03:53.010 --> 03:55.027
YEAH, NOW.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.017
[SIGHS]

03:58.019 --> 04:00.013
WOW! LET ME
LOOK AT YOU!

04:00.015 --> 04:03.003
CAN I JUST SAY,
YOU LOOK GREAT!

04:03.005 --> 04:05.023
LIFE IS SO WEIRD,
RIGHT?

04:05.025 --> 04:07.024
YESTERDAY I WAS IN L.A.,
AND NOW I'M HERE.

04:07.026 --> 04:09.020
AND ALREADY EVERYTHING'S
GOING LIKE THIS.

04:09.022 --> 04:13.027
AND I CAN JUST TELL
IT'S GONNA GO LIKE THIS!

04:15.000 --> 04:17.026
UM, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT,
EXACTLY?

04:17.028 --> 04:20.001
I'M TALKING ABOUT
MAKING MOVIES--

04:20.003 --> 04:22.004
A POWERPUFF MOVIE!

04:24.017 --> 04:26.015
AND HERE'S THE CATCH:

04:26.017 --> 04:29.025
YOU 3 ARE GONNA STAR
AS YOURSELVES!

04:29.027 --> 04:30.018
YEAH!

04:30.020 --> 04:31.025
ALL RIGHT! WOO!

04:31.027 --> 04:33.026
Bernstein:
I SAW THE LITTLE ARTICLE
IN THE TIMES

04:33.028 --> 04:34.024
ABOUT THE BANK HEIST,

04:34.026 --> 04:36.010
AND IT JUST CLICKED
RIGHT HERE.

04:36.012 --> 04:37.019
AND THE WHEELS
STARTED TURNING.

04:37.021 --> 04:39.008
'CAUSE THINK ABOUT IT--
THERE'S 3 OF YOU,

04:39.010 --> 04:40.012
SO IT WOULDN'T BE
THAT TWO THING.

04:40.014 --> 04:42.008
YOU KNOW, EVERYBODY'S
DOING THAT TWO THING,

04:42.010 --> 04:43.016
YOU KNOW?

04:43.018 --> 04:44.019
HUH?

04:44.021 --> 04:45.028
HELLO? WHO?

04:46.000 --> 04:47.023
OH, HI.

04:47.025 --> 04:49.006
OH, NOTHING.
I'M JUST HAVING LUNCH

04:49.008 --> 04:52.023
WITH THE NEXT 3 BIGGEST
STARS IN HOLLYWOOD.

04:53.025 --> 04:55.014
SURE THING.
CALL YOU BACK.

04:55.016 --> 04:56.027
BUH-BYE.

04:56.029 --> 04:57.029
WHERE WAS I?

04:58.001 --> 04:58.022
OH, YES.

04:58.024 --> 05:00.000
NOW I MUST WARN YOU,

05:00.002 --> 05:02.006
YOU SAY YES
TO DOING THIS MOVIE,

05:02.008 --> 05:03.015
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE RICH,

05:03.017 --> 05:05.003
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE FAMOUS.

05:05.005 --> 05:05.024
YES!

05:05.026 --> 05:06.029
HEY,
WAIT A SECOND!

05:07.001 --> 05:09.007
WE NEED TO THINK
ABOUT THIS
A LITTLE FIRST.

05:09.009 --> 05:10.029
OH, PROFESSOR!

05:11.001 --> 05:12.002
NO, NO, GIRLS.

05:12.004 --> 05:14.002
IT'S YOUR FATHER'S
DECISION,

05:14.004 --> 05:16.026
AND HE ALONE KNOWS
WHAT'S BEST FOR HIS GIRLS.

05:16.028 --> 05:17.029
BUT I TELL YOU...

05:18.001 --> 05:19.013
I CERTAINLY WOULDN'T
WANT TO BE THOUGHT OF

05:19.015 --> 05:22.028
AS THE TYPE OF PARENT
WHO JEALOUSLY HOLDS
HIS CHILDREN BACK

05:23.000 --> 05:25.018
FROM FULFILLING
THEIR POTENTIAL.

05:33.013 --> 05:35.017
JUST SIGN HERE.

05:36.019 --> 05:38.004
AND HERE...

05:38.006 --> 05:39.017
AND HERE...

05:39.019 --> 05:40.027
AND HERE...

05:40.029 --> 05:43.025
AND ONCE MORE HERE.

05:53.021 --> 05:55.023
WOW! OUR OWN MOVIE!

05:55.025 --> 05:57.014
YEAH, AND FINALLY
WE'LL GET

05:57.016 --> 05:59.025
THE RECOGNITION
WE DESERVE.

05:59.027 --> 06:00.028
AND THE PREMIERE!

06:01.000 --> 06:04.003
OH, MAYBE I'LL GET
A CHANCE TO MEET LEO!

06:04.005 --> 06:06.010
AND OUR NAME IN LIGHTS!

06:06.012 --> 06:08.004
STARRING BLOSSOM.

06:08.006 --> 06:10.011
I'D GET TOP BILLING,
OF COURSE.

06:10.013 --> 06:11.004
SAYS WHO?

06:11.006 --> 06:12.017
WELL, I AM THE LEADER.

06:12.019 --> 06:15.026
NU-UH! I'M JUST
AS IMPORTANT AS YOU.

06:15.028 --> 06:16.029
[GIGGLES]

06:17.001 --> 06:17.020
LEO.

06:17.022 --> 06:18.023
COME ON, BUTTERCUP.

06:18.025 --> 06:21.019
I'M THE ONLY REASON
MR. BERNSTEIN IS HERE.

06:21.021 --> 06:23.004
HA! OH, YEAH?

06:23.006 --> 06:24.020
WANT TO FIGHT ABOUT IT?

06:24.022 --> 06:27.011
[GIRLS ARGUING]

06:29.021 --> 06:32.000
Mayor: WELL, GOLLY GEE,
MR. BERNSTEIN,

06:32.002 --> 06:35.017
YOU WANT PERMITS TO FILM
IN THE TOWNSVILLE BANK

06:35.019 --> 06:37.002
AND THE USE OF
ALL ITS MONEY

06:37.004 --> 06:42.009
AND FULL POLICE JURISDICTION
IN A 4-MILE RADIUS?

06:43.005 --> 06:44.013
SO WHAT'S
THE PROBLEM?

06:44.015 --> 06:46.015
WELL, IT'S KIND
OF A LOT, ISN'T IT?

06:46.017 --> 06:48.024
LOOK, MR. MAYOR,
I UNDERSTAND
HOW YOU FEEL.

06:48.026 --> 06:52.006
I MEAN, WHEN MR. S.
CAME TO ME WITH THAT
BIG WAR PICTURE

06:52.008 --> 06:53.010
AND NOBODY
WOULD TOUCH IT,

06:53.012 --> 06:54.020
I HAD FEARS,
I HAD DOUBTS.

06:54.022 --> 06:58.001
BUT DID I LET THAT
STOP ME FROM DOING
WHAT I BELIEVED?

06:58.003 --> 06:59.018
HECK NO!
AND WE KNOCKED

06:59.020 --> 07:01.004
THE PANTS OFF 'EM
WITH THAT ONE.

07:01.006 --> 07:04.000
AND NOW...
NOW WHEN I ASK YOU,

07:04.002 --> 07:05.018
YOU, A TRULY
BEAUTIFUL MAN

07:05.020 --> 07:09.017
WITH THE CLASS
AND CHARM OF A YOUNG
EDWARD G. ROBINSON--

07:09.019 --> 07:11.021
OH! HA HA!
WELL, THANK YOU.

07:11.023 --> 07:12.027
UH...

07:12.029 --> 07:15.003
WHO SHOULD PROBABLY BE
STARRING IN THIS PICTURE.

07:15.005 --> 07:16.025
AND DON'T THINK
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

07:16.027 --> 07:18.016
THAT'S VERY POSSIBLE.

07:18.018 --> 07:21.018
AND NOW,
NOW WHEN I ASK YOU...

07:21.020 --> 07:23.025
DOWN ON ONE KNEE...

07:23.027 --> 07:28.010
FOR A FEW LOUSY PERMITS
FOR A TINY LITTLE MOVIE!

07:28.012 --> 07:29.022
OH, I'LL DO IT!

07:29.024 --> 07:32.014
MS. BELLUM,
DRAW UP THE PERMITS
FOR MR. BERNSTEIN.

07:32.016 --> 07:36.018
Bernstein on intercom:
CAN WE GET SOME COFFEE,
TOO, THERE, TOOTS?

07:50.019 --> 07:53.027
YES, FOLKS,
RIGHT HERE IN
OUR OWN BACKYARD,

07:53.029 --> 07:55.020
OUR OWN PIECE
OF HOLLYWOOD.

07:55.022 --> 07:56.020
IF YOU LOOK
BEHIND ME,

07:56.022 --> 07:58.015
YOU'LL SEE ALL
THE CAMERAS AND CREWS

07:58.017 --> 08:01.004
SETTING UP FOR
THE POWERPUFF GIRL MOVIE.

08:01.006 --> 08:04.013
SO, HOW LONG HAVE
YOU TWO BEEN WORKING
HERE AT THIS BANK?

08:04.015 --> 08:06.026
UM, ABOUT 7 YEARS.

08:06.028 --> 08:09.013
OH, YOU'RE GONNA DO
JUST FINE.

08:09.015 --> 08:11.022
WE'RE GONNA NEED
TO HIRE SOME ACTORS

08:11.024 --> 08:13.006
WHO LOOK LIKE
REAL TELLERS.

08:13.008 --> 08:15.001
OK, PEOPLE,
CAST AND CREW ONLY.

08:15.003 --> 08:16.002
EVERYBODY OUT.

08:16.004 --> 08:18.009
HEY, LET ME KNOW
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING.

08:18.011 --> 08:19.010
DONNIE!

08:19.012 --> 08:21.023
WE'RE GONNA NEED
A SECURITY GUARD, TOO.

08:21.025 --> 08:23.023
THIS GUY STINKS.

08:27.008 --> 08:28.016
NOW, IF YOU LOOK
BEHIND ME,

08:28.018 --> 08:32.008
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS
ARE JUST ARRIVING.

08:32.018 --> 08:35.012
THAT'S RIGHT!
WHO'S THE BADDEST?

08:35.014 --> 08:37.000
LOOK, I KNOW
IT'S YOUR BANK

08:37.002 --> 08:38.011
AND YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE,

08:38.013 --> 08:41.016
BUT WE HAVE TO USE
THE ACTUAL MONEY
FOR REALITY'S SAKE.

08:41.018 --> 08:43.017
UH, SIR, THE GIRLS
JUST ARRIVED.

08:43.019 --> 08:45.000
YEAH, THANK YOU.
RUN ALONG NOW.

08:45.002 --> 08:49.003
I'LL TAKE FULL RESPONSIBILITY
FOR THE CASH MYSELF.

08:49.005 --> 08:50.020
WELL, AS YOU KNOW,

08:50.022 --> 08:52.000
I'M THE TOUGHEST.

08:52.002 --> 08:54.025
YEAH, BUT YOU'RE
THE WORST ACTOR.

08:54.027 --> 08:57.029
SO, WHAT DO
YOU THINK OF
MY GIRLS?

08:58.001 --> 08:59.009
HIS GIRLS. HUMPH.

08:59.011 --> 09:02.003
YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN TELLING
THEM FOR YEARS

09:02.005 --> 09:04.002
THAT THEY HAVE
NATURAL TALENT.

09:04.004 --> 09:06.017
HEY, BUT WE JUST
MET YOU YESTERDAY.

09:06.019 --> 09:07.014
ALL RIGHT, HONEY,

09:07.016 --> 09:08.026
THE GROWNUPS
ARE TALKING NOW,

09:08.028 --> 09:11.019
SO YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO BE QUIET.

09:11.027 --> 09:13.029
HA HA HA!
KIDS.

09:14.001 --> 09:15.001
WHERE WAS I?

09:15.003 --> 09:17.002
BUT WE DID JUST
MEET HIM YESTERDAY,

09:17.004 --> 09:18.006
DIDN'T WE?

09:18.008 --> 09:21.014
I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU
TO KEEP YOUR MOUTH SHUT!

09:22.016 --> 09:26.008
MR. BERNSTEIN,
WE NEED TO HAVE A LITTLE TALK.

09:26.010 --> 09:27.010
COME ON,
BUBBLES.

09:27.012 --> 09:28.027
YOU'RE GONNA
MESS IT UP
FOR EVERYBODY.

09:28.029 --> 09:29.027
YEAH.

09:29.029 --> 09:31.015
OK.

09:32.016 --> 09:33.015
Man on radio:
I'LL TELL YOU,

09:33.017 --> 09:35.022
THE WORD IS THAT
THIS BERNIE BERNSTEIN

09:35.024 --> 09:36.026
IS HOT, HOT, HOT.

09:36.028 --> 09:40.000
HE IS MOVING UP THE POWER LIST
IN HOLLYWOOD.

09:40.002 --> 09:42.027
ANYBODY WANT
TO TALK ABOUT BERNIE--

09:48.002 --> 09:50.018
[SHOUTING]

09:58.009 --> 09:59.005
LISTEN, BUSTER,

09:59.007 --> 10:01.006
I NEED TO SEE
MR. BERNSTEIN,

10:01.008 --> 10:03.001
AND I MEAN NOW.
SEE?

10:03.003 --> 10:03.028
SURE THING.

10:04.000 --> 10:06.005
JUST TRY HIS TRAILER
OUT BACK.

10:06.007 --> 10:07.010
FINE!

10:07.012 --> 10:09.001
THANK YOU.

10:18.004 --> 10:19.015
EXCUSE ME,
IS MR. BERNSTEIN--

10:19.017 --> 10:20.014
Woman: OH, NO!

10:20.016 --> 10:22.003
UH, PARDON ME.
HAVE YOU--

10:22.005 --> 10:22.028
Woman: NO!

10:23.000 --> 10:24.000
HI, HAVE YOU SEEN--

10:24.002 --> 10:24.024
Man: AAH! NO!

10:24.026 --> 10:25.028
EXCUSE ME,
I'M LOOKING--

10:26.000 --> 10:27.023
Man: SORRY, BUDDY.

10:28.018 --> 10:29.016
Bernstein:
THIS HAS GOT TO BE

10:29.018 --> 10:31.006
THE GREATEST SCAM
WE'VE EVER PULLED.

10:31.008 --> 10:32.026
THE PEOPLE OF TOWNSVILLE
HAVE GOT TO BE

10:32.028 --> 10:36.005
THE MOST GULLIBLE BUNCH
OF SAPS I'VE EVER SEEN.

10:36.007 --> 10:37.019
AS IF ANYONE WOULD
REALLY BE INTERESTED

10:37.021 --> 10:40.020
IN MAKING A MOVIE
ABOUT THE POWERPUFF GIRLS!

10:40.022 --> 10:42.010
I LOVE HOW YOU TOLD THEM
YOU NEEDED TO USE

10:42.012 --> 10:44.017
THE REAL MONEY
FOR REALITY'S SAKE.

10:44.019 --> 10:45.017
HA HA HA!

10:45.019 --> 10:47.025
GOSH, HOW I'D LOVE
TO SEE THEIR FACES

10:47.027 --> 10:49.027
WHEN THEY FIND OUT
THAT THERE IS NO MOVIE,

10:49.029 --> 10:51.026
AND IT WAS ALL
JUST A BIG SCAM

10:51.028 --> 10:54.008
TO STEAL THE BANK'S MONEY.

10:54.021 --> 10:55.029
Narrator: OH, NO!

10:56.001 --> 10:57.026
BERNIE BERNSTEIN
A FRAUD?

10:57.028 --> 11:00.015
AND I WAS PROMISED A PART
IN THAT MOVIE!

11:00.017 --> 11:03.024
WELL, PROFESSOR,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

11:09.027 --> 11:12.005
JOINING US NOW,
WITH AN EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

11:12.007 --> 11:14.011
LIVE, ON-SET
FROM HIS DRESSING ROOM,

11:14.013 --> 11:16.004
THE MAYOR OF TOWNSVILLE.

11:16.006 --> 11:19.019
SO, MR. MAYOR,
WILL THIS BE YOUR FIRST
EXPERIENCE WITH ACTING?

11:19.021 --> 11:22.028
OH, NO. I STUDIED
ACTING FOR YEARS.

11:23.000 --> 11:24.012
OH, REALLY?
WHERE?

11:24.014 --> 11:25.024
TOWNSVILLE
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL.

11:25.026 --> 11:28.017
MR. MAYOR,
THEY'RE READY FOR YOU
ON THE SET.

11:28.019 --> 11:30.010
GOTTA GO.

11:36.027 --> 11:38.007
HEY, AM I GLAD TO
SEE YOU.

11:38.009 --> 11:39.015
SOMETHING TERRIBLE'S
HAPPENING.

11:39.017 --> 11:41.013
I NEED TO GET
IN TOUCH WITH
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS.

11:41.015 --> 11:42.012
YOU SEE--

11:42.014 --> 11:44.014
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, BUDDY.
SLOW DOWN.

11:44.016 --> 11:46.013
FIRST OF ALL,
WE'RE NOT COPS.

11:46.015 --> 11:47.025
WE'RE ACTORS.

11:47.027 --> 11:49.013
WE'RE WORKING
ON THE MOVIE.

11:49.015 --> 11:50.014
AND SECONDLY,

11:50.016 --> 11:52.004
YOU AIN'T GONNA FIND
NO COP AROUND HERE

11:52.006 --> 11:54.009
FOR ABOUT 4 MILES.

11:56.007 --> 11:58.002
ALL RIGHT, GIRLS,
PAY CLOSE ATTENTION.

11:58.004 --> 11:59.012
THIS IS HOW THIS
SHOT'S GONNA WORK.

11:59.014 --> 12:00.014
YOU 3 WILL COME IN

12:00.016 --> 12:02.016
THROUGH THE BREAKAWAY WALL,
RIGHT THERE.

12:02.018 --> 12:03.022
BREAKAWAY? HA!

12:03.024 --> 12:06.026
WE DON'T NEED
A BREAKAWAY WALL.

12:07.009 --> 12:09.005
RIGHT. SO,
LIKE I SAID,

12:09.007 --> 12:11.009
YOU 3 WILL COME THROUGH
THE BREAKAWAY WALL.

12:11.011 --> 12:12.016
YOU'LL ZIP OVER HERE,

12:12.018 --> 12:14.016
DO THE LITTLE FIGHT THING
WITH THE STUNT MEN HERE.

12:14.018 --> 12:15.020
YADDA YADDA YADDA.

12:15.022 --> 12:19.005
AND THEN--OH, DONNIE,
BRING IN THE MAYOR.

12:19.007 --> 12:21.022
HEY! I DON'T EVEN
HAVE MY SCRIPT YET.

12:21.024 --> 12:23.000
KNOW WHAT?

12:23.002 --> 12:25.007
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

12:25.023 --> 12:27.005
YOU GUYS ALL SET?
YUP!

12:27.007 --> 12:29.023
OK, THEY GAG
AND TAKE THE MAYOR
HOSTAGE,

12:29.025 --> 12:31.026
AND YOU LET 'EM GO.
ANY QUESTIONS?

12:31.028 --> 12:32.024
LET THEM GO?

12:32.026 --> 12:35.014
UH, WE JUST CAN'T
LET THEM GO.

12:35.016 --> 12:36.016
NOW, RELAX, HON,

12:36.018 --> 12:37.018
YOU'RE GONNA GET THEM
IN THE NEXT SCENE.

12:37.020 --> 12:41.003
TRUST ME, BABE,
IT WILL BE A LONG MOVIE.

12:53.021 --> 12:55.021
UM, HI.

12:55.023 --> 12:57.018
HOW'S IT GOING?

13:02.023 --> 13:04.002
[WHISTLING]

13:04.004 --> 13:08.010
SO, THEY SHOOTING
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS
MOVIE IN THERE?

13:08.012 --> 13:10.013
UH, YEAH.

13:21.021 --> 13:26.026
YOU KNOW, I INVENTED
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS.

13:26.028 --> 13:27.025
REALLY?

13:27.027 --> 13:32.014
YEAH. YOU KNOW,
IN MY LAB AT HOME.

13:33.024 --> 13:35.014
WHAT?

13:39.012 --> 13:40.021
SO YOU GONNA
LET ME IN?

13:40.023 --> 13:42.008
NAH.

13:43.002 --> 13:45.020
AND ACTION!

13:47.026 --> 13:50.022
Bernstein:
OK, GIRLS, NOW!

13:50.024 --> 13:52.009
OH!

13:52.011 --> 13:53.020
HEY, YOU BAD GUYS,

13:53.022 --> 13:55.016
PREPARE TO GET BLACK EYES.

13:55.018 --> 13:57.016
UM, BERNIE,
CAN WE TRY THAT AGAIN?

13:57.018 --> 13:59.016
IT JUST DIDN'T FEEL ORGANIC.

13:59.018 --> 14:00.025
[SIGHS]

14:00.027 --> 14:03.003
YEAH, SURE.
WHY NOT?

14:05.003 --> 14:06.020
HMM.

14:07.014 --> 14:10.023
LOOK, THERE'S ONLY
ONE PART FOR A DOG
IN THIS PICTURE,

14:10.025 --> 14:12.027
AND I TALK.

14:12.029 --> 14:13.022
STICK 'EM UP!

14:13.024 --> 14:15.021
CHEESE IT!
IT IS THE COPS!

14:15.023 --> 14:17.004
NOBODY MOVE!
NOBODY MOVE!

14:17.006 --> 14:18.010
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!

14:18.012 --> 14:19.028
YOU JERKS!

14:20.000 --> 14:21.006
THOSE GIRLS ARE STRONG.

14:21.008 --> 14:22.022
PROFESSOR UTONIUM?

14:22.024 --> 14:24.028
ALL RIGHT,
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

14:25.000 --> 14:25.028
UM...

14:26.000 --> 14:27.012
HELP. SAVE ME?

14:27.014 --> 14:28.024
HA HA HA HA!

14:28.026 --> 14:30.011
GREAT!
THAT WAS REALLY GOOD.

14:30.013 --> 14:34.016
BUT WE'RE ACTUALLY
ONLY LOOKING FOR A WOMAN
AT THIS TIME. THANK YOU.

14:36.016 --> 14:39.021
GET READY...
TO EAT LEAD!

14:41.016 --> 14:42.005
NOW?

14:42.007 --> 14:43.016
Bernstein: YES! YES!

14:43.018 --> 14:45.006
YOU PICKED
THE WRONG DAY

14:45.008 --> 14:47.027
TO MESS WITH
THIS SISTER...

14:47.029 --> 14:50.003
MISTER!

14:50.005 --> 14:51.011
[BERNSTEIN CLEARS THROAT]

14:51.013 --> 14:53.001
OH, YEAH!

14:53.008 --> 14:54.009
WHAT?

14:54.011 --> 14:56.029
I JUST DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD SAY THAT LINE.

14:57.010 --> 14:58.017
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO THINK.

14:58.019 --> 14:59.020
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO
ACT.

14:59.022 --> 15:01.000
BERNIE,
I'M NOT COMFORTABLE

15:01.002 --> 15:03.008
WITH BUTTERCUP SAYING
THE "SISTER, MISTER" LINE.

15:03.010 --> 15:05.010
I'M THE LEADER.
I SHOULD SAY IT.

15:05.012 --> 15:07.001
WELL, I DON'T HAVE
ANY LINES,

15:07.003 --> 15:10.001
AND I'M THE CUTEST
AND THE FAVORITE!

15:10.003 --> 15:13.012
I CAN'T WORK
LIKE THIS!

15:14.007 --> 15:17.010
OK, I GUESS WE'LL TAKE
A 5-MINUTE BREAK.

15:17.012 --> 15:18.021
IN THIS NEXT SHOT,
YOU'RE GONNA PLAY

15:18.023 --> 15:20.000
THE TELLERS
IN THE BACKGROUND.

15:20.002 --> 15:21.018
THE ACTION'S GONNA
TAKE PLACE HERE
IN FRONT OF YOU,

15:21.020 --> 15:23.009
AND THE CAMERA
WILL BE BEHIND ME,
THERE.

15:23.011 --> 15:24.012
SO JUST TRY
AND ACT NATURAL,

15:24.014 --> 15:26.019
AND DON'T
DO ANYTHING
TOO DISTRACTING.

15:26.021 --> 15:29.023
OK? YOU'RE GONNA DO
JUST FINE.

15:29.025 --> 15:32.001
NOTHING TOO
DISTRACTING, HUH?

15:32.003 --> 15:33.012
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

15:33.014 --> 15:34.013
WHAT'S THAT, TOOTS?

15:34.015 --> 15:36.007
OH, NOTHING, DEAR.

15:36.009 --> 15:37.026
PLACES, EVERYONE.

15:37.028 --> 15:39.028
POWERPUFFS.

15:40.026 --> 15:42.008
FEELING BETTER,
BUTTERCUP?

15:42.010 --> 15:44.004
YES, BERNIE.

15:44.006 --> 15:46.009
GOOD, ALL RIGHT.
ACTION!

15:46.011 --> 15:49.015
COME ANY CLOSER,
AND THE MAYOR GETS IT.

15:49.017 --> 15:50.015
[WHISPERING]
Blossom!

15:50.017 --> 15:51.023
OH, NO!

15:51.025 --> 15:54.015
IT LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE GONNA
GET AWAY WITH IT, GIRLS.

15:54.017 --> 15:55.015
[WHISPERING]
Blossom!

15:55.017 --> 15:56.016
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

15:56.018 --> 15:57.028
Professor: BLOSSOM,
THERE'S SOMETHING

15:58.000 --> 15:59.019
VERY WRONG
GOING ON HERE.

15:59.021 --> 16:01.000
Blossom: WHY ARE YOU
DRESSED LIKE A WOMAN?

16:01.002 --> 16:03.001
WOULD SOMEBODY
MIND TELLING ME

16:03.003 --> 16:07.008
WHAT THE HECK
IS GOING ON HERE?

16:07.010 --> 16:08.013
I'D BE GLAD TO!

16:08.015 --> 16:10.024
YOU, SIR, MR. BERNSTEIN,
ARE A FRAUD, A FAKE,

16:10.026 --> 16:11.025
A CON ARTIST!

16:11.027 --> 16:13.008
AND I, FOR ONE,
AM NOT THE TYPE OF MAN

16:13.010 --> 16:14.024
WHO WILL STAND BY
AND LET A CROOK--EXCUSE ME--

16:14.026 --> 16:19.016
A CROOK LIKE YOU STEAL FROM
THE GOOD PEOPLE OF TOWNSVILLE.

16:19.018 --> 16:21.016
BY GOLLY,
SHE'S GOOD.

16:21.018 --> 16:22.024
AND CUTE, TOO!

16:22.026 --> 16:23.023
[GROWLS]

16:23.025 --> 16:25.017
AND I, SIR,
AM NOT THE TYPE OF MAN

16:25.019 --> 16:29.028
WHO WOULD LET A CREEP LIKE YOU
EXPLOIT HIS CHILDREN!

16:30.000 --> 16:31.029
HUMPH!

16:34.018 --> 16:35.016
[CLICKS TONGUE]

16:35.018 --> 16:36.028
OH, PROFESSOR!

16:37.000 --> 16:38.023
WHY DIDN'T YOU
JUST SAY SOMETHING?

16:38.025 --> 16:42.024
I MEAN, IF YOU
WANTED TO BE IN
THE MOVIE SO BAD,

16:42.026 --> 16:44.010
ALL YOU HAD TO DO
WAS ASK

16:44.012 --> 16:46.016
INSTEAD OF TRYING
TO EMBARRASS ME

16:46.018 --> 16:47.018
AND FRANKLY,
YOURSELF,

16:47.020 --> 16:49.023
WITH THESE WILD
ALLEGATIONS.

16:49.025 --> 16:51.013
AW, PROFESSOR.

16:51.015 --> 16:53.016
WHAT?
DON'T LISTEN TO HIM!

16:53.018 --> 16:55.007
I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'S ALL A CON.

16:55.009 --> 16:56.029
DR. PLUTONIUM,
PLEASE!

16:57.001 --> 16:58.006
IF YOU ARE QUITE
FINISHED,

16:58.008 --> 17:00.025
WE HAVE A LOT
OF WORK TO DO.

17:02.000 --> 17:02.023
LOOK!

17:02.025 --> 17:04.022
SEE, NO FILM
IN THE CAMERA!

17:04.024 --> 17:05.025
SEE, NO FILM!
HA HA!

17:05.027 --> 17:06.025
THERE, I GOTCHA!

17:06.027 --> 17:08.010
YOU CAN'T MAKE A MOVIE
WITHOUT FILM!

17:08.012 --> 17:10.014
FRAUD! FAKE!
CON MAN!

17:10.016 --> 17:12.023
[STUTTERING]

17:12.025 --> 17:14.024
WE'RE, UH, REHEARSING.

17:14.026 --> 17:18.012
YOU DON'T USE FILM
FOR REHEARSAL.

17:18.014 --> 17:21.007
SO BACK OFF.

17:25.007 --> 17:27.004
LOOK! SEE, IT'S BLANK!

17:27.006 --> 17:28.006
NO SCRIPT!

17:28.008 --> 17:29.024
HOW DO YOU MAKE A MOVIE
WITH NO SCRIPT?

17:29.026 --> 17:31.028
SCRIPT?
WHO NEEDS A SCRIPT?

17:32.000 --> 17:34.010
WE'RE GOING FOR
A CINEMA VERITE,

17:34.012 --> 17:36.000
REALITY KIND OF THING.

17:36.002 --> 17:37.008
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

17:37.010 --> 17:38.012
GIRLS, PLEASE.

17:38.014 --> 17:39.028
YOU'VE GOT
TO BELIEVE ME.

17:40.000 --> 17:42.012
I HEARD HIM MYSELF.

17:43.024 --> 17:45.020
I BELIEVE YOU,
PROFESSOR.

17:45.022 --> 17:46.020
HMM.

17:46.022 --> 17:48.005
BRAVO,
PROFESSOR.

17:48.007 --> 17:49.022
VALID POINTS,
ALL.

17:49.024 --> 17:52.017
BUT, IF THIS WEREN'T
A MOVIE SHOOT,

17:52.019 --> 17:54.018
BUT A HEIST,
AS YOU SAY--

17:54.020 --> 17:55.024
MAY I BORROW THIS,
SON?

17:55.026 --> 17:57.023
IF THIS WERE
ACTUALLY A HEIST,

17:57.025 --> 18:02.000
THEN WOULDN'T THIS GUN
INSTEAD HAVE REAL BULLETS?

18:02.002 --> 18:03.020
HMM?

18:03.022 --> 18:05.028
ALL RIGHT, NOBODY MOVE!

18:06.000 --> 18:07.004
AAH!

18:07.006 --> 18:08.010
OK, ME AND THE MAYOR

18:08.012 --> 18:09.016
ARE GONNA TAKE
A LITTLE RIDE.

18:09.018 --> 18:11.025
SO DON'T DO
ANYTHING STUPID.

18:11.027 --> 18:13.016
THE MAYOR!

18:13.018 --> 18:15.001
GIRLS!

18:15.003 --> 18:17.016
'SCUSE ME, I'LL JUST
BE TAKING THIS.

18:17.018 --> 18:19.020
HEY, WE'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO SHOOT THE CHASE SCENE

18:19.022 --> 18:21.017
FOR ANOTHER HOUR!

18:23.014 --> 18:24.025
WHICH WAY DID THEY GO?

18:24.027 --> 18:26.026
THAT WAY!

18:29.011 --> 18:31.001
HANG TIGHT, MAYOR.

18:54.011 --> 18:55.022
EH, BERNIE?

18:55.024 --> 18:56.028
LOOK, BERNIE!

18:57.000 --> 18:59.003
WHAT?

19:02.024 --> 19:03.026
EASY, BERNIE.

19:03.028 --> 19:05.022
DON'T DO ANYTHING STUPID.

19:05.024 --> 19:08.003
NOBODY MOVE,

19:08.005 --> 19:09.021
OR THE MAYOR GETS IT.

19:09.023 --> 19:11.004
CUT!

19:11.006 --> 19:13.003
COME ON,
NOT LIKE THAT!

19:13.005 --> 19:15.009
GIVE IT
SOME FEELING,
LIKE THIS!

19:15.011 --> 19:17.002
[IMITATING EDWARD G. ROBINSON]
ALL RIGHT, SEE?

19:17.004 --> 19:21.019
NOBODY MOVE OR THE MAYOR HERE
GETS IT, SEE?

19:29.029 --> 19:32.002
LOOK, PROFESSOR,
BABY!

19:32.004 --> 19:32.029
I CAN EXPLAIN!

19:33.001 --> 19:34.028
IT'S NOT WHAT
YOU THINK, MAN.

19:35.000 --> 19:37.001
CAN WE TALK
ABOUT IT, PLEASE?

19:37.003 --> 19:38.025
NO, NO!

19:39.028 --> 19:40.024
ALL RIGHT!

19:40.026 --> 19:43.016
AND THAT'S A WRAP,
MR. BERNSTEIN.

19:43.018 --> 19:45.008
PROFESSOR,
YOU DID IT!

19:45.010 --> 19:47.013
OH, PROFESSOR,
WE'RE SORRY...

19:47.015 --> 19:49.017
FOR LETTING OURSELVES
GET SO SUCKED INTO

19:49.019 --> 19:50.024
THAT DUMB MOVIE STUFF.

19:50.026 --> 19:54.018
I MEAN, WHAT A DUMB IDEA
TO MAKE A POWERPUFF MOVIE.

19:54.020 --> 19:58.011
WELL, YEAH, THAT WAS
A DUMB IDEA, BUT THIS...

19:58.013 --> 20:00.009
THIS WOULD MAKE
A GREAT MOVIE--

20:00.011 --> 20:01.016
THE POWERPUFF GIRLS
MOVIE

20:01.018 --> 20:03.010
ABOUT THE MAKING OF
THE POWERPUFF MOVIE!

20:03.012 --> 20:06.012
AND I'LL ARRIVE
AT THE END WITH
THE FINISHING BLOW,

20:06.014 --> 20:08.009
SHOWING OFF
MY AWESOME PHYSIQUE.

20:08.011 --> 20:10.012
OF COURSE, I'LL PROBABLY
HAVE TO WORK OUT A LITTLE

20:10.014 --> 20:11.014
AND HIT THE TANNING SALON,

20:11.016 --> 20:13.027
GET MY GRAY TOUCHED UP
AT THE TEMPLES...

20:13.029 --> 20:15.009
Narrator: OH, BROTHER.

20:15.011 --> 20:18.019
SO ONCE AGAIN,
I GUESS THE DAY IS SAVED

20:18.021 --> 20:21.025
THANKS TO THE SMART GUY
IN THE DRESS.

20:21.027 --> 20:25.026
UGH. HE LOOKS
JUST LIKE MY MOM!

